{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3dc2a006-77b9-4b43-9d88-ff22dcfb7cba","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014Q7UWdhu4MKxbj538JqcYQ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring .NET crash dumps"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013i5SrYMr7bD8nMmAAbYZg7","name":"grep","arguments":{"pattern":"createdump|DbgMiniDump|DbgCreatedump|CrashDump","-i":true,"head_limit":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"createdump|DbgMiniDump|DbgCreatedump|CrashDump"}],"interactionId":"6c608fb5-bb1d-4489-8561-6ee2fda32710","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me explore if there's any relevant configuration in the repository first, then provide the answer.\n\nLet me think about what's needed:\n\n1. **Environment variables** for .NET crash dump configuration\n2. **Kubernetes pod spec changes** (volume mounts, env vars, etc.)\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dumps, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — controls the dump type (Mini, Heap, Triage, or Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — specifies where to write the dump file\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` — enables diagnostics output from createdump\n- `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport` — generates a JSON crash report for NativeAOT apps\n- The `DOTNET_` prefix is the current standard for .NET 6+, replacing the older `COMPlus_` convention\n\nFor NativeAOT on .NET 8+, I need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to point to the createdump tool location. I'll need to configure a volume for persisting the crash dumps and set up the appropriate environment variables in the pod spec.","outputTokens":587,"requestId":"D80A:1E89:1BB9E0F:1EF1DB0:69FBF034"},"id":"c5557e6d-1129-4c54-af83-b034d752f27d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:52:03.532